The gun is a rescue, the previous owner had done a very bad job trying to shorten the rifle to 18". When I received the rifle the barrel looked like it had been cut with an angle grinder. The barrel has since been re-cut and crowned with a full width 11 degree target crown. The barrel has been floated and the gun has been completely gone over and cleaned up. The barrel length currently sits right at 17" if measured off the face of the receiver. The gun came with a 1:10 twist barrel from the factory and as it is pictured it shoots right around 3/4" at 100 yards with 168 grain ammo. The scope is an older Redfield 3-9x40 that I've had lying around that I tossed onto the gun. The scope has some decent outer wear on it but it still holds a zero and tracks straight. I was ringing silhouette steel at 500 yards with the gun just two weekends ago. 

$525 located in Graham NC

title: For Sale:  Ruger LCP, Gen-2 (.380 ACP)
postcontent:
Gently used Ruger LCP, Gen-2 (.380 ACP).  You can see from the photos that this gun is in excellent shape.  It has less than 50 rounds through it.  Its slim, tiny profile makes it perfect for concealed carry.  It really does disappear in any pocket or purse.

You may be sure that this is actually a Gen-2 model of the LCP because there is no dash in the serial number of this gun.  The Gen-2 version of the LCP also has better sights and a new, vastly improved trigger which has a much shorter and lighter trigger pull than the original version of the LCP.  To enhance the grip on this small gun, I’ve added a Talon grip.

To further enhance this gun, I’ve installed a side-mounted red laser on it from LaserLyte.  The laser is easily removed if you don’t wish to use it.  You can remove the laser by replacing the mounting pins with the original frame pins which I am including with the gun.  The whole process takes no more than five minutes using allen-key tools (also provided) and it doesn’t require any gun-smith skills at all.  I’m a klutz and I did it quite easily.

Also includes a nice Remora holster for IWB carry and a Boraii trigger-cover holster for deep concealment pocket carry, factory lock with two keys, the 6-round mag supplied by Ruger (with flat floorplate and pinky extension floorplate) plus a second Ruger factory 6-round mag (also with flat floorplate and pinky extension floorplate), factory box and all paperwork that came from the factory (as shown in photo). 

I prefer a face-to-face transfer in east Tennessee without shipping.  Must be a legal buyer, 21 or over with a valid TN driver’s license or permit. If the ad is still up, the gun is still available.

Cash only…sorry, I’m not looking for a trade or low-ball offers.

title: For Sale:  Pepsi machine hidden gun safe
postcontent: Up for sale is an old Pepsi machine that has been stripped of all of the internal mechanical and refrigeration parts and converted into a gun safe. From the outside it looks just like an old vending machine. On the inside is a custom made gun cabinet. The old fluorescent backlight has been replaced with efficient LED strips that operate with a small remote control. On the inside there is more LED lights that are on a magnetic switch. The lights turn on as soon as you open the door and turn off when the door is closed. The inside cabinet of the machine is appx. 62” tall 35” wide and 17” deep. It will hold a lot of guns. It is actually wide enough to fit a AR15 long ways on the top shelf. The top shelf is ½” solid pine, not plywood, plenty sturdy enough to hold ammo and any other valuable gear you would like to store with your firearms. The small corner shelf is for shorter rifles like AK's and AR's and the underside of it can be used for ammo/gear storage also. There is also a large compartment with a removable cover at the bottom of the machine where the refrigeration used to be. It needs be used for bulk ammo storage or filled with sand bags to give the machine weight and keep it from getting top heavy. The cabinet is set up for and includes 8 Rifle Rods. Do a google search for them and you will see how they work, you can order more rods if needed from amazon, ebay ect. The outside of the machine is in original condition and is pretty good for its age but it is not perfect, it does have scratches from everyday use. It would look great in a garage, basement, game room or man cave The idea behind storing your firearms in an old vending machine is “hiding in plain sight” If a thief breaks into your house looking for valuables he is going to walk right past the Pepsi machine and look for the safe in the closet. asking $750 but will listen to offers. REDACTED

I need to sell my Ruger Redhawk .44 Magnum revolver, in like-new condition.  It is 6-shot, stainless steel, with a 7.5" barrel. I bought this gun new in 1983, and I still have the original box in perfect condition.  The gun has the original factory grips.

The Ruger Redhawk revolver was Ruger's first double-action revolver specifically designed for the powerful .44 Magnum cartridge. It has many advanced features such as a triple-locking cylinder, a unique single-spring mechanism for lighter trigger pull, replaceable front sights and adjustable rear sights, with all-stainless steel construction.

The Redhawk is reinforced to handle extra stress, making it very popular for use by handloaders as it handles the hottest of magnum loads with ease.  This makes the Redhawk popular as a bear defense gun among hunters and trappers.

This Redhawk was fitted in the past with a Simmons Pro-Hunter 4 X 32 handgun scope, with a silver matte finish to match the gun.    It's waterproof, shockproof, fog-proof, and will easily stand up to the recoil of a .44 Magnum.  It has Weaver-style bases.   I have the original box and papers that came with the scope.

The included B-Square scope mount was made especially for the Ruger Redhawk and clamps firmly on the barrel.  It will not move under recoil.  The silver finish matches the gun and scope.

Two holsters are included in this package:   The Western-style holster and cartridge belt is made by El Paso Saddlery.  There are loops for 47 cartridges, and the holster is lined with suede leather to protect the gun finish.

A nylon shoulder holster is also included for the pistol with the scope mounted.  It is comfortable and supports the pistol for hunting and field carry.  There is also a zipper carrying case for the pistol.

I'm including 50 rounds of .44 magnum ammunition for practice and familiarity.  Do you think a .44 Magnum is too much gun for you?  Then shoot .44 Special ammo with much less recoil and noise.  The .44 Special recoil is negligible in this heavy gun.

This Ruger Redhawk package must be seen to be appreciated.  The pictures just don't do it justice.  Respond to this ad with your name and phone number and I'll call you so we can talk and make arrangements for you to see it.  You will not be disappointed.
